trend_summary: Across the time-series, woodland retreats while cropland blocks broaden, indicating steady agricultural expansion. Built-up footprints increase only marginally in scattered hamlets along main roads, with no emergence of a continuous urban core. Overall character remains distinctly rural and low-density.
notable_changes: Progressive clearing of forest in the west and centre, replaced by rectangular cropland.
Field parcels merge and enlarge, suggesting mechanised farming consolidation.
Minor residential infill and a few new farmsteads along the primary road network.
A straighter, brighter linear corridor appears, indicating a road upgrade or new track.
Higher proportion of bare soil in the most recent image, reflecting intensified cultivation cycles.
